narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: I became better at summarizing and analyzing my work, as well as giving helpful critique to my fellow classmates.
I learned that independent research is difficult! And that I should always be pushing myself further, and asking myself challenging questions about my own research.

We mostly learned how to pace ourselves for the large project that is the thesis. I appreciated the insights and feedback from my classmates about my work, and I enjoyed the opportunity to learn what the other majors are studying. Feimster was great at guiding us and being helpful and flexible. This class does what it needs to do, which is help you to start your thesis.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: I actually really like how much freedom we had to focus on our research.
I wish we had more class and that Prof Feimster spoke more! She's wonderful.
I think it was great as it was; it did what it needed to do.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes! Great way to prepare for your project and hear from other students in the major.
